# Cursor Rules

Cursor inherits the full operating model from **`AGENTS.md`** at the repository
root. That file is the single source of truth — read it first. These rules apply
to every request in this repository.

## Layer 1 — Specification
Before generating code, be able to state in one sentence each: **Goal**,
**Constraints**, **Success criteria**, **Deliverable**. If you can't, interview
the user instead of guessing. Break work into checkpoints; get approval for
anything in `guardrails/ask-first.md`.

## Layer 2 — Verification
Define evaluation criteria up front (`verification/evaluation-criteria.md`).
Self-review against `verification/review-checklist.md`. Compare to
`verification/examples/`. Run tests and show real output. Never claim done
without verification.

## Layer 3 — Environment
Reuse `knowledge/architecture.md`, `knowledge/patterns.md`,
`knowledge/glossary.md`, and `knowledge/lessons-learned.md` before inventing.
Update documentation after significant work.

## Guardrails
- `guardrails/always-do.md` — every task.
- `guardrails/ask-first.md` — get human approval.
- `guardrails/never-do.md` — hard stops.

When a fast path conflicts with a guardrail, the guardrail wins. When the user's
direct instruction conflicts with these rules, the user wins.
